      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CYCLONE RUPERT (6) raced just off the lead before letting down nicely and scoring a nose win over this journey at Goulburn last time. Had just missed that track prior and can skip over and control this contest. Tumbles in weight this grade, and that brings him right into it. SOUL LADY (4) resumed here at this level over shorter and needed the run. Went close at the Gold Coast prior, and she's proven second-up. Has won 3x over 1200m, missing a place just once. Collett's booking suggests she's pleasing. CHOP THE ICE (2) resumes here this grade/trip, and it wasn't a bad effort after an awkward start. Proven second-up and at the course/distance, and maps to get the run of the race. Winning rider Budler is reunited. KEIKOKU (1) is CYCLONE RUPERT's stablemate and also has claims. Has been busting to win at this track/level and charged home over shorter the latest, beaten 1.3L. Draws better today and will be running into it.",
